Maybe add a bit more explanation:
// Skip older versions since they don't support "getTableNamesByType" in ThriftHiveMetastore#getAllViews
// and so information_schema.views does not include translated Hive views properly

BTW, it still worthwhile to run the test with older Hive versions, just the assertions would be different -- to document current behavior & prevent regressions.
How would it look like if you used getHiveVersionMajor() on per-assertion basis?
kind of like https://github.com/prestosql/presto/blob/3c5b5b053affa6cf093e7f4cbca0bb26d9bfb380/presto-product-tests/src/main/java/io/prestosql/tests/hive/TestHiveTableStatistics.java#L129-L131

